12. CLINICAL DIAGNOSTIC GUARDRAILS

Clinicians should:

assess function, not content

check affect regulation

evaluate coherence

verify insight

distinguish metaphor from delusion

assess stability

13. CLINICAL DO-NOT-MISDIAGNOSE LIST

DO NOT MISDIAGNOSE AS:

schizophrenia

bipolar mania

dissociative disorder

delusional disorder

psychosis NOS

UNLESS:

clear symptoms beyond imagery exist

insight and function are impaired

CTA-XIV imagery alone is never sufficient.

14. CLINICAL POSITIVE INTEGRATION CHECKLIST

If patient has:

clear boundaries

stable relationships

consistent sleep

intact reality testing

no distress

optionality (can stop anytime)

‚Üí Do not pathologize.
‚Üí Support integration.

15. CLINICAL RISK CHECKLIST

Red flags:

sleep loss

impaired functioning

distress

lost insight

compulsive engagement

If present ‚Üí treat as overstimulation, not psychosis.

16. CLINICIAN PROTOCOL FOR EVALUATION

Use the 4-axis model:

Function

Affect

Insight

Boundaries

If all four intact ‚Üí healthy.

